# Performance & context (ECC-inspired, Cursor)

## Model choice (flexible)

- Use a **faster / cheaper** model for straightforward, narrow tasks when your Cursor plan allows it.
- Use a **more capable** model for architecture, subtle bugs, security-sensitive review, and large refactors.

## Context window

- As context fills, **re-read only what you need**; avoid pasting huge files repeatedly.
- Prefer **targeted** tests and searches over loading entire trees when possible.

## When the build or tests fail

1. Read the **first failing error** carefully.
2. Fix **incrementally**; re-run the **narrowest** command that reproduces (e.g. single test file).
3. Avoid large speculative changes without a red/green signal.

There is no Cursor equivalent of Claude Code’s `~/.claude/settings.json` hook runner—rely on **discipline + CI + local scripts**.
